reserve M2 for (Matrix of n,( REAL ));
theorem
(((M1 is  Positive & M2 is  Negative) & |: M1 :| is_less_than |: M2 :|) implies ( M1 + M2 ) is  Negative)
proof
assume that
A1: M1 is  Positive
and
A2: M2 is  Negative
and
A3: |: M1 :| is_less_than |: M2 :|;
A4: ( Indices M1 ) = [: ( Seg n ),( Seg n ) :] by MATRIX_1:24;
A5: ( Indices ( M1 + M2 ) ) = [: ( Seg n ),( Seg n ) :] by MATRIX_1:24;
A6: ( Indices M2 ) = [: ( Seg n ),( Seg n ) :] by MATRIX_1:24;
(for i holds (for j holds ([ i,j ] in ( Indices ( M1 + M2 ) ) implies ( ( M1 + M2 ) * (i,j) ) < ( 0 ))))
proof
let i;
let j;
assume A7: [ i,j ] in ( Indices ( M1 + M2 ) );
then [ i,j ] in ( Indices |: M1 :| ) by A4,A5,CKB33:1;
then ( |: M1 :| * (i,j) ) < ( |: M2 :| * (i,j) ) by A3,CKB5:def 1;
then ( abs ( M1 * (i,j) ) ) < ( |: M2 :| * (i,j) ) by A4,A5,A7,CKB7:def 1;
then ( abs ( M1 * (i,j) ) ) < ( abs ( M2 * (i,j) ) ) by A6,A5,A7,CKB7:def 1;
then A8: ( ( abs ( M1 * (i,j) ) ) - ( abs ( M2 * (i,j) ) ) ) < ( ( abs ( M2 * (i,j) ) ) - ( abs ( M2 * (i,j) ) ) ) by XREAL_1:9;
( M2 * (i,j) ) < ( 0 ) by A2,A6,A5,A7,CKB2:def 1;
then A9: ( - ( M2 * (i,j) ) ) = ( abs ( M2 * (i,j) ) ) by ABSVALUE:def 1;
( M1 * (i,j) ) > ( 0 ) by A1,A4,A5,A7,CKB1:def 1;
then ( abs ( M1 * (i,j) ) ) = ( M1 * (i,j) ) by ABSVALUE:def 1;
then ( ( M1 * (i,j) ) + ( M2 * (i,j) ) ) = ( ( abs ( M1 * (i,j) ) ) - ( abs ( M2 * (i,j) ) ) ) by A9;
hence thesis by A4,A5,A7,A8,MATRIXR1:25;
end;
hence thesis by CKB2:def 1;
